{"questionId":"35034021","questionHtml":"<p>Find the area of the youngest child’s land.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Distance from (2, 2) to (1, 3) is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {{1^2} + {1^2}}&nbsp; = \\sqrt 2 \"> <msqrt> <mrow> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </msqrt> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mn>2</mn> </msqrt> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So length of youngest child’s square is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2\\frac{{\\sqrt 2 }}{2} = \\sqrt 2 \"> <mn>2</mn> <mfrac> <mrow> <msqrt> <mn>2</mn> </msqrt> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mn>2</mn> </msqrt> </math></span> and thus area is 2.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35034021","referenceCode":"EXM.2.SL.TZ0.4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the area of the youngest child’s land.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}